The paper proposes a learning approach for signal detection in sparse code multiple access (SCMA) systems using a deep neural network. This involves unfolding the message passing algorithm (MPA) and treating the weights as parameters of a neural network. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, as it deals with signal detection and communication systems. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that the paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of emerging Artificial Intelligence (AI) chips, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the proposed method involves refining the network weights corresponding to the edges of a factor graph, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
